<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.monokultur.dk/wp-content/apostats_ibn_warraq_100503.doc" class="external text" title="http://www.monokultur.dk/wp-content/apostats_ibn_warraq_100503.doc" rel="nofollow">"Edward Said and the Saidists: or Third World Intellectual Terrorism",</a> by <a href="/wiki/Ibn_Warraq" title="Ibn Warraq">Ibn Warraq</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> MacKenzie, J.M., 1995, <i>Orientalism: history, theory and the arts</i>, Manchester, Manchester University Press, page 11</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> MacKenzie, J.M., 1995, <i>Orientalism: history, theory and the arts</i>, Manchester, Manchester University Press</li>
</ol>
</div>


